<dl id="n03091b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03091b">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03091b"> 91(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Scotus sapiens</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[CHAPTER VIII, The Irish Schools]</font> The word &lsquo;<mark>sapiens</mark>&rsquo; so frequently employed in the early literature is applied to a learned man who was versed at once in sacred and profane literature. <small> J.M. Flood, <a name="JMFI" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JMFI"><cite title="source">Ireland: Its Saints and Scholars</cite></a> (n.d) 80</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
